article.headline: Kansas St. 99, Chicago St. 68
article.story: MANHATTAN, Kan. -- Fred Brown scored a game-high 26 points off the bench to lead Kansas State over Chicago State 99-68 on Monday night. Darren Kent had 13 points and 12 rebounds and Jacob Pullen added 12 points for the Wildcats (11-3). Kansas State had six players in double figures in its final nonconference game of the season. David Holston led Chicago State (8-8) with 18 points. John Cantrell and Carl Montgomery added 12 points each. The Cougars kept the game close in the first half before a basket by Pullen sparked a 22-2 Wildcat run that put Chicago State away for good. Leading 49-31 at halftime, Kansas State made the most of the Cougars' foul trouble in the second period. Chicago State committed its 10th team foul with 15:52 left to play and the Wildcats capitalized on the opportunity, hitting 20-of-23 free throw attempts.
